To run celery workers as daemons:

1. Copy config/celeryd_init to etc/init.d/celeryd
2. Setup permissions on /etc/init.d/celeryd:

sudo chmod 755 /etc/init.d/celeryd
sudo chown root:root /etc/init.d/celeryd

3. Create configuration file:

Copy config/celeryd to etc/default/celeryd

4. Set config values appropriately

5. Run sudo /etc/init.d/celeryd start/stop/restart

Reference:
https://pythad.github.io/articles/2016-12/how-to-run-celery-as-a-daemon-in-production
